  "overview": {
    "value": "Tianlong-3 is a two-stage, medium-lift orbital launch vehicle developed by Space Pioneer, designed to be partially reusable with a first stage capable of autonomous vertical landing and reuse up to 10 times. It is 71 m tall, 3.8 m in diameter, and rated to lift 17 t to low Earth orbit or 14 t to a sun-synchronous orbit. Its maiden flight, on 3 April 2026 from Jiuquan, suffered an anomaly during first-stage flight; booster recovery was not attempted on this flight.",
